      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a driver-focused example featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine, generating 320 hp and 273 lb-ft of torque. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. This iteration benefits from VarioCam Plus, optimizing valve lift and timing for a robust power band. The chassis remains taut, utilizing its signature rear-engine layout for superior mechanical grip, supported by a multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts. Braking is handled by four-piston monoblock calipers over vented rotors, ensuring consistent deceleration. Well-maintained and mechanically sound, this 911 offers the visceral feedback and analog steering precision that defines the era.",
